    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on a high-upside slate today, led by **Kyle Tucker** (76.51) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.76). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Rea and a wind-out forecast that boosts his slugging potential. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a strong platoon advantage against Gallen, with his projected efficiency elevated by a prime spot in the heart of the order. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.45) rounds out our top-tier trio; while he faces a formidable arm in Cantillo, his elite xwOBA and dynamic platoon edge make him an essential anchor for our offensive floor.\n\nEfficiency remains the priority for our middle-of-the-pack starters like **Miguel Vargas** (60.21) and **Andy Pages** (60.94). **Miguel Vargas** draws a favorable matchup against the lower-tier command of Irvin, allowing him to outperform his base projection. Conversely, while **Gunnar Henderson** carries a respectable 53.01 score, he faces an elite challenge in Crochet; the park factors provide a necessary boost, but the matchup against a high-end lefty necessitates tempered expectations. **Coby Mayo** (47.14) represents our most difficult sit decision, coming remarkably close to the utility slot. Ultimately, **Josh Jung** (59.81) earned the start over **Coby Mayo** due to a superior individual SP matchup profile, as we prioritize minimizing exposure to the Crochet-led pitching staff.\n\nWe are monitoring the risk profile of **Drake Baldwin**, whose score of 46.69 is heavily suppressed by a daunting matchup against Wheeler. While **Drake Baldwin** is a standard play, his sub-50 score serves as a reminder to monitor late-game defensive substitutions or pinch-hit risks. We are keeping a close eye on **Nasim Nunez** (47.95) and **Heliot Ramos** (49.30) as well, as their status as marginal starts suggests that even minor shifts in weather or batting order could move them into the bench-preservation zone. Our remaining depth, including **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jordan Westburg**, and **Marcell Ozuna**, remains available for tactical swaps should any of our active starters face unexpected lineup shifts.",
